    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_1021_acs_analchem_0c03895__task_001/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "ViMMS 2.0 is a software framework that can be used to develop new fragmentation strategies in metabolomics completely in-silico as well as on mass spectrometry instruments. The framework allows users to generate chemical objects (produced synthetically or extracted from existing mzML files) and simulate a tandem mass spectrometry process",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms ViMMS can simulate MS acquisition and generate chemical objects, but does not specifically mention HMDB database as a source for chemicals. Paper states chemicals can be generated 'synthetically' or 'extracted from existing mzML files' but does not name HMDB as a supported source. The capability to produce mzML output is not explicitly stated in passages.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-21105-joss-03990",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_001",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Can ViMMS simulate a full-scan MS1 acquisition on a set of known chemical compounds sampled from the HMDB database and produce a valid mzML output file?",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T12:48:07.877866+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_1021_acs_analchem_0c03895__task_001/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Chemicals can be generated in different ways: either in a purely synthetic manner (e.g. sampling their properties from databases or fixed statistical distributions) or by construction from existing data (mzML files) via the extraction of RoI traces.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper discusses input from mzML files and simulation of MS acquisition, but does not explicitly confirm that ViMMS outputs mzML files. The framework simulates tandem mass spectrometry but output format is not specified in provided passages.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-21105-joss-03990",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_001",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "expected_outputs",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "mzML file containing MS1-only scans from the full-scan simulation",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T12:48:07.877866+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_1021_acs_analchem_0c03895__task_001/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Code is provided to compute various evaluation metrics, such as coverage and intensities of fragmented precursors. This allows users to benchmark different controller implementations comparatively.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper mentions evaluation metrics and benchmarking capabilities but does not specifically name 'EvaluationData' object or confirm pickle file output format. The concept of storing evaluation data is implied but the specific data structure and serialization format are not mentioned.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-21105-joss-03990",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_001",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "expected_outputs",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Pickle file containing EvaluationData object with chemicals, generated scans, and fragmentation events",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
