    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/hmdb-metabolite-extraction/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Chemicals are input objects to the simulation process in ViMMS 2.0, and can be generated in different ways: either in a purely synthetic manner (e.g. sampling their properties from databases or fixed statistical distributions) or by construction from existing data (mzML files) via the extraction of RoI traces. The framework allows users to plug in modular classes that specify parameters of chemicals, such as the distribution of their m/z values, RT, intensities, chromatographic shapes and associated MS2 spectra",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms ViMMS 2.0 supports chemical generation from databases and allows m/z and intensity specification, but does NOT explicitly mention HMDB, DatabaseFormulaSampler, or HMDB-specific filtering utilities. The paper discusses synthetic generation and mzML extraction, not HMDB extraction specifically.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-21105-joss-03990",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "hmdb-metabolite-extraction",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
