    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/mass-spectrometer-simulator-configuration/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "ViMMS 2.0 is a software framework that can be used to develop new fragmentation strategies in metabolomics completely in-silico as well as on mass spectrometry instruments. The framework allows users to generate chemical objects (produced synthetically or extracted from existing mzML files) and simulate a tandem mass spectrometry process, where different fragmentation strategies can be rapidly implemented, tested and evaluated.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms ViMMS simulates tandem MS/MS acquisition and chemical mixture handling. However, passages do not explicitly mention 'polarity' or 'ionization mode' as configurable parameters in the simulator. The paper focuses on fragmentation strategy development rather than detailed MS instrument parameter configuration (polarity, ionization mode, detector parameters). This is a narrower scope than the card claims.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-21105-joss-03990",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "mass-spectrometer-simulator-configuration",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Configure a virtual mass spectrometer instance within the ViMMS framework to simulate tandem MS/MS acquisition on a chemical mixture with specified polarity, ionization mode, and detector parameters.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T12:54:05.390197+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/mass-spectrometer-simulator-configuration/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The improved modularity in ViMMS 2.0 allows many aspects of the framework to be swapped out with alternative implementations, including classes that generate various aspects of chemicals (e.g. measured m/z, RT, intensity) for simulation (Figure 1A), mass spectrometry simulation (Figure 1B), controllers that implement different fragmentation strategies (Figure 1C), as well as the environmental context to run them all (Figure 1D).",
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes modular MS simulation but does not explicitly detail polarity, ionization mode, or detector parameter configuration. The framework is designed for fragmentation strategy development, not comprehensive instrument parameter specification.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-21105-joss-03990",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "mass-spectrometer-simulator-configuration",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Configure a virtual mass spectrometer instance within the ViMMS framework to simulate tandem MS/MS acquisition on a chemical mixture with specified polarity, ionization mode, and detector parameters.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T12:54:05.390197+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/mass-spectrometer-simulator-configuration/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "ViMMS 2.0 is a software framework that can be used to develop new fragmentation strategies in metabolomics completely in-silico as well as on mass spectrometry instruments. The framework allows users to generate chemical objects (produced synthetically or extracted from existing mzML files) and simulate a tandem mass spectrometry process",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms ViMMS provides mass spectrometry simulation. However, the specific class name 'IndependentMassSpectrometer' is not mentioned in the provided passages. The paper describes the simulator framework and modular architecture but does not name this specific class in the excerpts provided.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-21105-joss-03990",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "mass-spectrometer-simulator-configuration",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "ViMMS \u2014 Core framework providing IndependentMassSpectrometer class and virtual acquisition simulation engine",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T12:54:05.390197+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/mass-spectrometer-simulator-configuration/003",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "ViMMS 2.0 is distributed as a Python package that can be easily installed using pip. We require Python 3.0 or higher to run the framework. It depends on common packages such as numpy, scipy and pandas.",
      "asbval:note": "Confirmed: ViMMS is a Python package requiring Python 3.0+.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-21105-joss-03990",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "mass-spectrometer-simulator-configuration",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Python \u2014 Language for instantiating and configuring the mass spectrometer object",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T12:54:05.390197+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
