      "asbval:note": "Paper describes ViMMS 2.0 as supporting chemical generation from databases and m/z-related parameters, but does not explicitly mention HMDB filtering by m/z range constraints as a primary use case. The paper focuses on fragmentation strategy development and simulation, not database filtering workflows. No mention of 'DatabaseFormulaSampler' class or HMDB-specific filtering utilities found in passages.",
