    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/molecular-formula-database-filtering/004",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "ViMMS 2.0 is a software framework that can be used to develop new fragmentation strategies in metabolomics completely in-silico as well as on mass spectrometry instruments. The framework allows users to generate chemical objects (produced synthetically or extracted from existing mzML files) and simulate a tandem mass spectrometry process, where different fragmentation strategies can be rapidly implemented, tested and evaluated.",
