    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/vimms-controller-configuration-and-execution/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "ViMMS 2.0 is a software framework that can be used to develop new fragmentation strategies in metabolomics completely in-silico as well as on mass spectrometry instruments. The framework allows users to generate chemical objects (produced synthetically or extracted from existing mzML files) and simulate a tandem mass spectrometry process, where different fragmentation strategies can be rapidly implemented, tested and evaluated.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper explicitly describes simulating fragmentation strategies and extracting from/working with mzML files. Controllers are implemented and executed in the framework.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-21105-joss-03990",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "vimms-controller-configuration-and-execution",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Configure and execute a ViMMS controller to simulate MS/MS fragmentation acquisition strategies on a virtual mass spectrometer, then export the resulting scan data as mzML files.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T12:57:11.874933+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/vimms-controller-configuration-and-execution/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "A common challenge faced by computational researchers with an interest in improving fragmentation strategies in tandem-mass-spectrometry-based metabolomics is the lack of access to and the high cost of running MS instruments... To lower this barrier, we present Virtual Metabolomics Mass Spectrometer (ViMMS) 2.0, a programmable and modular framework that simulates the chemical generation process and the execution of fragmentation strategies in LC-MS/MS-based metabolomics.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper explicitly states ViMMS addresses the barrier of MS hardware access and enables rapid development of fragmentation strategies.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-21105-joss-03990",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "vimms-controller-configuration-and-execution",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "This skill bridges the gap between strategy design and evaluation by enabling rapid prototyping of data-dependent or data-independent acquisition methods without access to real MS hardware.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T12:57:11.874933+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/vimms-controller-configuration-and-execution/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Chemicals are input objects to the simulation process in ViMMS 2.0, and can be generated in different ways: either in a purely synthetic manner (e.g. sampling their properties from databases or fixed statistical distributions) or by construction from existing data (mzML files) via the extraction of RoI traces. The framework allows users to plug in modular classes that specify parameters of chemicals, such as the distribution of their m/z values, RT, intensities, chromatographic shapes and associated MS2 spectra.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes chemical input with m/z, RT, and intensities, but does not specifically name 'IndependentMassSpectrometer' class. Paper mentions 'mass spectrometer' and 'environment' classes but the specific class name is not confirmed in passages.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-21105-joss-03990",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "vimms-controller-configuration-and-execution",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "You have a set of chemical compounds (with known retention times and intensities) loaded into a ViMMS IndependentMassSpectrometer",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T12:57:11.874933+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/vimms-controller-configuration-and-execution/003",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Scan parameters control, for example, whether a controller flexibly targets a single precursor ion for fragmentation, in what is commonly known as data-dependent acquisition (DDA), or whether it instead covers a range of m/z values, potentially fragmenting many precursor ions (data-independent acquisition; DIA).",
      "asbval:note": "Paper explicitly describes DDA and DIA strategies. Full-scan MS1 is implied in the context of survey scans mentioned in the abstract.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-21105-joss-03990",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "vimms-controller-configuration-and-execution",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "simulate a specific MS/MS fragmentation strategy (e.g., data-dependent acquisition, full-scan MS1, or targeted acquisition)",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T12:57:11.874933+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/vimms-controller-configuration-and-execution/004",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Code is provided to compute various evaluation metrics, such as coverage and intensities of fragmented precursors. This allows users to benchmark different controller implementations comparatively.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes evaluation metrics and benchmarking capabilities for generated scan data.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-21105-joss-03990",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "vimms-controller-configuration-and-execution",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "generate reproducible MS/MS scan data for downstream evaluation",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
